    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-01-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-01-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="303"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d303">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Buck</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-01-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 271.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch No. 392 of the 29th ultimo, reporting the present attitude of the
                    Japanese Government respecting the registration of perpetual leases in foreign
                    settlements in Japan.</p>
                <p>In reply I have to say that the attitude of the Japanese Government in the
                    matter, as it is now reported by you, is unobjectionable.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
